{"sha": "a84c62a7f13cd26faaf79a3a77d30706b73afaf8", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmE4NGM2MmE3ZjEzY2QyNmZhYWY3OWEzYTc3ZDMwNzA2YjczYWZhZjg=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Alexander Kuleshov", "email": "kuleshovmail@gmail.com", "date": "2017-10-10T10:36:53Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Alexander Kuleshov", "email": "kuleshovmail@gmail.com", "date": "2017-10-10T18:00:18Z"}, "message": "Fix path to x.py in configure.py script\n\nWe may see a help message in the end of the output of the ./configure script:\n\n$ ./configure\nconfigure: processing command line\nconfigure:\nconfigure: build.configure-args := []\nconfigure:\nconfigure: writing `config.toml` in current directory\nconfigure:\nconfigure: run `python ./src/bootstrap/x.py --help`\nconfigure:\n\nbut the x.py script is actually in the rust root directory and\nexecuting of such help string will give us error:\n\n$ python ./src/bootstrap/x.py --help\npython: can't open file './src/bootstrap/x.py': [Errno 2] No such file\nor directory\n\nThis patch fixes path to the x.py script in the output of the ./configure", "tree": {"sha": "64589a96634a2f4229fa1c4ff73861696d605692", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/64589a96634a2f4229fa1c4ff73861696d605692"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/a84c62a7f13cd26faaf79a3a77d30706b73afaf8", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/a84c62a7f13cd26faaf79a3a77d30706b73afaf8", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/a84c62a7f13cd26faaf79a3a77d30706b73afaf8", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/a84c62a7f13cd26faaf79a3a77d30706b73afaf8/comments", "author": {"login": "0xAX", "id": 2699235, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI2OTkyMzU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2699235?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/0xAX", "h